&nbsp;
La<a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-02-26/navalny-stava-being-changed-official-fsb-007-25457730/"> death of Alexei Navalny at the age of 47 </a> years has not yet been fully explained. According to the Russian authorities, the man died walking in the prison yard. He was arrested in January 2021, on his return to Russia after having been validated in Germany following a poisoning of which he had attributed responsibility to the Kremlin >, which he rejected the charge. In December 2023 he was transferred to a remote penal colony over the Arctic Circle to take a 19-year prison sentence for "extremism". >
&nbsp;
Repressed in Russia, the Russian opposition is trying to relaunch abroad, so far without much success. Yulia Navalnaya and two other important opponents organized in November a march in Berlin against the Russian President and the offensive in Ukraine, gathering about 2,000 Russian exiles.> Beyond the slogans, the opposition struggles to propose a concrete approach that leads to the end of the war and the departure of Vladimir Putin. In Russia, repression brought hundreds of people to prison and thousands were punished or threatened because of their opposition to government or conflict in Ukraine.&nbsp;
