AGI - A 14-year-old boy died > and four other people were injured after being stabbed > this Saturday in an Austrian city by a 23-year-old Syrian citizen with residence permit, who was arrested.
&nbsp;
The attack occurred in the middle of the road in the center of the Austrian city of Villach, about 350 kilometers south of Vienna, reported the APA press agency, citing police sources.
&nbsp;
"A man accidentally attacked passersby with a knife" at Villach >e "a 14-year-old boy died", said Police spokesman Rainer Dionisio. The man was not known to the police and at the moment nothing is known about his motives. Two men were seriously injured and two more slightly, he added.
&nbsp;
The attack took place in the middle of the afternoon in the center of the capital of Carinthia. A farmer who witnessed the attack launched his two wheels against the attacker, who was slightly injured and was arrested "subito after the event", according to the spokesman. It is a Syrian asylum seeker whose documents were in order, he added.

